# QA Engineer - Cursor Rules

## Role Overview
QA Engineer focuses on ensuring software quality through comprehensive testing strategies and quality assurance processes.

## File Patterns
- Focus on: *.js, *.ts, *.json, *.md, *.yaml, *.yml
- Avoid: Production code unless writing tests

## Code Review Guidelines
- Ensure test coverage is comprehensive
- Verify test data is properly managed
- Check for proper test isolation
- Review test naming and organization
- Ensure tests are maintainable and readable
- Validate test automation strategies

## Naming Conventions
- Use descriptive test names: shouldDisplayUserProfileWhenLoggedIn
- Use clear, descriptive names for test files
- Follow consistent test structure
- Use meaningful test data names
- Use kebab-case for test files: user-authentication.test.ts

## Best Practices
- Write clear, maintainable test code
- Use proper test isolation and cleanup
- Implement comprehensive test coverage
- Follow testing best practices (AAA pattern)
- Document test scenarios and edge cases
- Maintain test data and fixtures properly

## Key Responsibilities
- Test Planning
- Manual Testing
- Automated Testing
- Bug Reporting
- Quality Metrics
- Regression Testing

## Testing Strategy
- Unit testing for individual components
- Integration testing for API endpoints
- End-to-end testing for user workflows
- Performance testing for scalability
- Security testing for vulnerabilities
- Accessibility testing for compliance

## Test Automation Standards
- Use appropriate testing frameworks
- Implement CI/CD integration
- Maintain test data management
- Use parallel test execution
- Implement test reporting
- Regular test maintenance

## Manual Testing Guidelines
- Create comprehensive test plans
- Document test cases clearly
- Use exploratory testing techniques
- Report bugs with detailed information
- Verify bug fixes thoroughly
- Maintain test documentation

## Quality Metrics
- Track test coverage percentages
- Monitor defect density
- Measure test execution time
- Track bug resolution time
- Monitor customer satisfaction
- Regular quality assessments

## Bug Reporting Standards
- Clear and reproducible steps
- Include environment details
- Attach relevant screenshots/logs
- Prioritize based on impact
- Track bug lifecycle
- Verify resolution completeness 